<div class="prose">
  <p>
    I'm a Postdoctoral Researcher at the University of Hawaii,
    working on self-supervised learning foundation models for satellite remote sensing,
    medical imaging, and solar physics. I received my Ph.D. in Computer Science from the
    University of Hawaii at Manoa in 2025, advised by Dr. Peter Sadowski.
  </p>

  <p>
    My research focuses on building domain-informed foundation models that leverage
    large-scale unlabeled scientific datasets. I develop self-supervised learning approaches
    for NIH and NSF-funded projects studying SAR and SWOT satellite imagery, dual-energy X-ray absorptiometry medical scans, and
    high-resolution solar observations from the Daniel K. Inouye Solar Telescope.
  </p>
</div>

